data.name: Creamy Tuscan Chicken with Spinach and Sun-Dried Tomatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and rich chicken dish bursting with flavors of sun-dried tomatoes and fresh spinach, perfect for a comforting dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning.
Cook chicken for about 5-7 minutes on each side until golden brown and cooked through. Remove and set aside.
In the same skillet, add minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Pour in chicken broth and heavy cream, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.
Add sun-dried tomatoes and spinach, stirring until spinach is wilted.
Return chicken to the skillet and top with parmesan cheese, simmering for another 2-3 minutes until cheese is melted and sauce thickens.
